## Limitations

The research is limited by the availability of online resources and the potential bias in historical interpretations. Some sources may present a Eurocentric view, focusing primarily on the experiences of Western countries, which may not fully represent the global impact of the war on civilians. Additionally, the lack of firsthand accounts from the period may limit the depth of understanding of the civilian experience during World War I.